stylometry: The broad and general management tradeoff decision when managing inventory is how to much to order and when to order.  When you purchase inventory you have to take into consideration demand.  Demand in many situations varies so you must do your best to estimate what you feel will be the demand.  Companies dont want to ever run out of products.  THey have to balance how much to order based on the demand, but they dont want to have excess inventory because holding costs will then eat up profit.  When you order inventory you have to figure out if there is an annual fixed cost or if there is a fixed cost everytime you place an order.  This will help you decide whether or not you are going to order more often or in smaller or larger quantities.  THe key for companies is to balance these to issues to benefit their company the most.
